3.00	Raimon_de_Miraval	Raimon de Miraval	Raimon de Miraval(h) (c. 1135/1160 – c. 1220) was a troubadour (fl. 1180–1220) and, according to his vida, "a poor knight from Carcassonne who owned less than a quarter of the castle of Miraval." Favoured by Raymond VI of Toulouse, he was also later associated with Peter II of Aragon and Alfonso VIII of Castile. His nom de plume was Audiart.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Raimon_de_Miraval.jpg/220px-Raimon_de_Miraval.jpg
